there are procedures for employees, students, and visitors to follow when handling injury or accident reports involving the university. employees (including student workers) should immediately report any work-related injury or illness to his or her supervisor. see workers’ compensation for more information. in the event of an accident or injury involving a student or visitor to the university, the highest priority must always be caring for the individual. student and visitor accident reporting is necessary to assist the university in proper investigation and follow-up measures to prevent further accidents and to assist with the injured person's own medical insurance. any reports that upd or other police agencies may file are also needed. all claims against san josé state university must be filed with the risk management department within six (6) months of the accident or incident date of occurrence. completed claim forms must be mailed or delivered to the address below along with a $25 claim filing fee. checks should be made out to "trustees of csu." visit the cal state university risk management and public safety website for further information and to obtain a claim form [pdf] . the california state university - office of the chancellor risk management and public safety 401 golden shore, 5th floor long beach, ca 90802-4210 phone: 408-924-1558 email: financeconnect@sjsu.edu finance and business services san josé state university 60 south market street suite 470 san josé, ca 95113 